# 8. Packet Fragmentation Scan

## Objective

Test simple firewall evasion.

## Command

```bash
sudo nmap -f <TARGET-IP>
```

## Output File

```bash
sudo nmap -f <TARGET-IP> -oN raw-output/fragmentation-scan.txt
```

## Explanation

- `-f` fragments packets into smaller pieces.
- May bypass poorly configured firewalls.
- Useful for IDS/Firewall evasion testing.

